MAMELODI Sundowns have confirmed the signing of a former Maritzburg United defender Brian Onyango who was recently unveiled by Tshakhuma Tsha Madzivhandila. The Kenyan centre-back penned a three-year deal with a two-year option to extend with Sundowns. “Brian Onyango has joined Mamelodi Sundowns on a three year deal with a two-year option to extend,” Sundowns said in a statement. “The Kenyan International joins Masandawana as a free agent, he last turned out for Maritzburg United. “The centre back comes with a wealth of international and local experience as he has played for Santos, the Team Of Choice and his national side. Onyango first moved to South Africa in 2012 to join the now ABC Motsepe based Santos.” 